Name: Sporting Vacations - Swimming
Page_Notes__c: This is a new page to be created - not a priority. From: Kristina Evelyn [mailto:kevelyn@caribsurf.com]  Sent: Thursday, January 09, 2014 11:53 AM To: Karen Allen Cc: Z M Evelyn Marketing Subject: Sporting vacations  Karen  Saw your sporting vacations section, http://www.totallybarbados.com/barbados/Travel/Barbados_Vacations/Barbados_Sporting_Vacations/  Would love if you guys could add swimming to the list:  There is our event Nov 2nd.  We are also hosting an international masters POOL meet preceding the open water event this year. Oct 27-30. Aquatic centre (no event name as yet) There are various swim groups and clubs who visit barbados for a hol and do swim events and training in the sea and at the Aquatic centre annually.   Eg every March ?Red Tide? a swim club from new york visits. I think there were about 40 swimmers in their group last year.  Other groups and individuals often contact the Flying Fish Masters Group and swim with them while visiting.  Note that there is an open water swim group that meets every week to swim carlisle bay and visitors to island oftem make contact through this group so they can swim also. https://www.facebook.com/OpenWaterSwimmingBarbados  Regards Kristina
